file=AI & Agents/anneal/logical/book-requirements.md · h=name: anneal-logical-book-requirements\ntype: logical\nstatus: built — 2 dedicated scripts + inherits Shared OS (2026-07-15)\nassigned_agent: anneal (AI & Agents / Lessons & Maintenance)\ndate_added: 2026-07-10\ndate_filled: 2026-07-15\n · p:=All logical scripts live in `Shared OS/logical/` (§13.5). Anneal owns 2 dedicated scripts for fleet measurement + staleness economics and inherits cross-agent scripts. This file is the only file in this folder.\n · tb=\| # \| Script \| Source Book 1 \| Book 1 URL \| Source Book 2 \| Book 2 URL \| Route \| · tb=\|---\|--------\|--------------\|------------\|---------------\|------------\|-------\| · tb=\| 1 \| `fleet_measurement.py` \| DeMarco, *Controlling Software Projects* (1982) \| [archive.org](https://archive.org/details/controllingsoftw0000dema) — FREE \| CETIC/Fenton & Pfleeger, *Software Metrics Overview* \| [cetic.be](https://www.cetic.be/IMG/pdf/Software_Metrics_Overview.pdf) — FREE \| B/C \| · tb=\| 2 \| `staleness_economics.py` \| DeMarco, *Controlling Software Projects* (1982) Ch.3,10-12,15-17 \| [archive.org](https://archive.org/details/controllingsoftw0000dema) — FREE \| CETIC/Fenton & Pfleeger, *Software Metrics Overview* \| [cetic.be](https://www.cetic.be/IMG/pdf/Software_Metrics_Overview.pdf) — FREE \| A/C \| · tb=\| Script \| Why Anneal Needs It \| · tb=\|--------\|---------------------\| · tb=\| `signal_detection.py` \| Drift detection for staleness trends over time \| · tb=\| `decision_analysis.py` \| MAUT for lesson impact assessment \| · tb=\| Previously Flagged (0.6) \| Status \| Script \| · tb=\|--------------------------\|--------\|--------\| · tb=\| Numeric staleness scoring (vs fixed 12-month flag) \| ✅ Cleared \| `staleness_economics.py` (doc_freshness with 3 decay models: exponential, logarithmic, linear) \| · tb=\| Knowledge coverage tracking \| ✅ Cleared \| `staleness_economics.py` (knowledge_coverage — breadth × depth × avg freshness) \| · tb=\| Edit-impact estimation (which skills cost most → audit priority) \| ✅ Cleared \| `staleness_economics.py` (edit_impact — staleness × references × usage × severity; ROI-prioritized) \| · tb=\| Audit priority ordering \| ✅ Cleared \| `staleness_economics.py` (audit_priority — staleness × references × edit_risk) \| · tb=\| Lesson-to-edit conversion-rate targets \| ✅ Cleared \| `staleness_economics.py` (lesson_cycle_economics — conversion/completion/staleness-loss rates per DeMarco Ch.15-17) \| · tb=\| Remediation cost estimation \| ✅ Cleared \| `staleness_economics.py` (remediation_cost_estimate per DeMarco Ch.11-12) \| · tb=\| Promote-to-production readiness gates \| ✅ Cleared \| `fleet_measurement.py` (promotion_readiness — 5-gate model per DeMarco Ch.6-8) \| · sm:=- **lesson-lifecycle** → imports `staleness_economics.py` (lesson_cycle_economics, remediation_cost_estimate)\n- **documentation-health** → imports `staleness_economics.py` (doc_freshness, knowledge_coverage, audit_priority)\n- **edit-impact-prioritization** → imports `staleness_economics.py` (edit_impact) + `fleet_measurement.py` (standards_effectiveness)\n